                "post_excerpt": "<div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">[metaslider_hide devices=\"desktop,laptop\"]<\/span> <h2 style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(236, 240, 241); line-height: 1em;\">Build a Workday That Actually Works<\/h2> <p data-start=\"452\" data-end=\"746\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">[\/metaslider_hide]<\/span><\/p> <p data-start=\"452\" data-end=\"746\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">[metaslider_hide devices=\"smartphone,tablet\"]<\/span><\/p> <h3 data-start=\"402\" data-end=\"450\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(236, 240, 241);\">Build a Workday That Actually Works<\/span><\/h3> <p style=\"line-height: 1;\" data-start=\"452\" data-end=\"746\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Remote work gives you flexibility, but it also removes structure. Without clear boundaries, work can easily spill into personal time&mdash;or distractions can take over your day. The key is designing a routine that matches your energy, not forcing yourself into a traditional 9&ndash;5 mindset.<\/span><\/p> <p data-start=\"748\" data-end=\"941\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">[\/metaslider_hide]<\/span><\/p> <\/div>",
